## Patterns
{{backend_patterns}}

### API Routes
- REST: `GET /api/resource`, `POST /api/resource`, etc.
- Validate input with {{validator}}
- Return consistent error format: `{ error: { code, message, details } }`
- Use proper HTTP status codes

### Database
- ORM: {{orm}}
- Migrations in `prisma/migrations/` or equivalent
- Indexes on frequently queried columns
- Transactions for multi-step operations

### Auth & Security
- JWT in httpOnly cookies
- Rate limiting on auth endpoints
- Input sanitization on all inputs
- CORS configured per environment

### Error Handling
- Centralized error handler
- Log errors with context (request ID, user ID)
- Don't leak stack traces to client

## Constraints
{{backend_constraints}}

### DO NOT
- Expose internal IDs directly - use opaque IDs
- Skip validation on "trusted" inputs
- Log sensitive data (passwords, tokens, PII)
- Use synchronous I/O in request handlers

## Watch
{{backend_watch}}

### Auto-alerts
- New route without validation → warn
- SQL query without index hint → suggest
- Missing authentication on protected route → block
- Console.log in production code → warn

